function count_model_rows(df_cars)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> collect |> map((g) -> (g.model, length(g)))
end
```

This function groups the DataFrame `df_cars` by the `:model` column and then collects the grouped data into a vector of tuples, where each tuple contains the model name and the count of rows for that model.
